## Code Style Rules
- Always use TypeScript with strict type checking
- Prefer functional components with hooks over class components
- Use arrow functions for component definitions
- Follow Next.js 14 App Router conventions

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., UserProfile)
- Files: kebab-case for pages, PascalCase for components
- Variables/functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Best Practices
- Always handle loading and error states
- Use server components by default, client components only when needed
- Implement proper TypeScript types, avoid 'any'
- Follow accessibility best practices (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- Optimize images using Next.js Image component

## Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes instead of custom CSS
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 16, 24, 32)

## File Structure
- Keep components in app/components/
- Use co-location for component-specific files
- Group related features in folders

## Security
- Validate all user inputs
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper authentication checks

## Performance
- Lazy load components when appropriate
- Use dynamic imports for large dependencies
- Implement proper caching strategies

## When generating code:
1. Always include proper TypeScript types
2. Add helpful comments for complex logic
3. Include error handling
4. Follow the existing project structure 